						               													<description>After a trip to Isla de Pascua (Easter Island), the author brings to us this game based on the inhabitants of the island and the extinction of them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Rapa-Nui tribes were isolated about 1000 years in a remote, tiny and volcanic island. There were a lack of resources and the population lived in a unstable balance with the environment, the rivalry between tribes and the collective society.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;THE GAME&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players manage the building of the 'moais' (these big sculptures with big faces, facing to the sea), using quarries, men, palm trees (to take wood) and even 'slaves'.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;I had heard from some testers that the mechanics of the game were very similar to Puerto Rico, but the only similarity is the 'role selection' phase.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is only available (rules and components) for Print &amp;amp; Play at: http://kokorin.wordpress.com/2008/06/15/rapa-nui/&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
